extracted_text:
The Suburban Residential (SR) district is the County's primary
district for suburban residential neighborhoods located along
primary roadways, shoreline areas, and in locations bordering
rural areas. The district has a one-acre minimum lot area
requirement, which is the basic threshold size for lots with on-
site wastewater systems.
llm_outputs.rationale: The purpose statement for the SR district explicitly states that it has a one-acre minimum lot area requirement. This is confirmed in the dimensional requirements table, which shows a minimum lot area of 1 acre for traditional development.
